<br>
My Nan died about 4 months ago.<br>
<br>
I found her in her flat with my mother, her daughter.  I did CPR and so on til the ambulance arrived, knowing all the time that it was way too late.<br>
<br>
I came home that night late and made a few posts on here about some nonsense or other to take my mind elsewhere.  My grieving process was completely screwed up and still is by a sense of guilt, not that there was anything I could have done.  I wrote and read the eulogy at her funeral and still havn't managed to grieve properly (writing this helps some).<br>
<br>
What I'm saying is, think about all the love over the years rather than the circumstances at the end.<br>
